cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with 3D reconstruction from endoscopy videos, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves surgical navigation, which is related to robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel loss design for dense descriptor learning, which involves machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions learning-based dense descriptors, which involves artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves Structure from Motion (SfM), which is related to graphics, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) another possible sub-category.
